.TH "igc_set_mac_filter_hw" 9 "igc_set_mac_filter_hw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
igc_set_mac_filter_hw \- Set MAC address filter in hardware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" igc_set_mac_filter_hw
.BI "(struct igc_adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "enum igc_mac_filter_type type "  ","
.BI "const u8 *addr "  ","
.BI "int queue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
Pointer to adapter where the filter should be set
.IP "index" 12
Filter index
.IP "type" 12
MAC address filter type (source or destination)
.IP "addr" 12
MAC address
.IP "queue" 12
If non-negative, queue assignment feature is enabled and frames
matching the filter are enqueued onto 'queue'. Otherwise, queue
assignment is disabled.
